I am a British student studying in America, at Lock Haven University. I am doing a research paper on how the Vietnam War affected peoples lives. Before I came to the U.S. all I knew about the war was from various movies, which appeared very simplistic. Now I am ashamed of my ignorance, and wish I had been taught more about the war, and it's affects, at school. I have the deepest respect for anyone who went to Vietnam. Please keep telling your stories, it is the only way people like me can begin to learn from them. I would very much like to hear from anyone who wishes to share their story with me. Thanks for your time. 
